summary: Re-watching the flashback scene and god TJ's mannerisms were so over-dramatic, like is it wrong to say even at 9 (or however old...
question: Re-watching the flashback scene and god TJ's mannerisms were so over-dramatic, like is it wrong to say even at 9 (or however old that scene is meant to be) that boy gives off THE BIGGEST gay vibes? It's so precious and adorable. Reminds me of my brother when he was younger as well.
answer: I don’t want to kill anyone’s gay vibes here but I think pretty much everyone seems to be forgetting that the reason TJ’s mannerisms were over dramatic in the flashback is because they were inaccurate. That flashback was not meant to show the actual series of events which took place on the little league team. It was Jonah’s telling of his memory that he had not spoken about in 7-ish years. And memories aren’t reliable. We warp our own memories to fit our own feelings and narratives. We romanticize happy memories in order to feel nostalgic. And we emphasize bad memories to rationalize our negative feelings related to them. So we still have absolutely no idea how young TJ behaved, we only know how Jonah (and his anxiety) remembered him.

summary: Ok I'm actually really interested in the Miranda coming back plot like most of us didn't really expect that
question: Ok I'm actually really interested in the Miranda coming back plot like most of us didn't really expect that
answer:
I don’t know why we didn’t talk more about that possibility. Here I was pushing for a Andi/Amber/Jonah storyline, there most people were reaching for the deleted Gabriel storyline….and of course it’s…………….Miranda. 

I’m not completely mad about it yet though. Definitely interested to see if it actually ends up feeling like something that moves the story forward, or if it’s just a filler plot to take up time before the wedding.
